<TITLE> Probe ordered into cause of fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 13 (bdnews24.com)A three-member investigation committee has been formed after the country's biggest shopping mall Basundhara City turned into a towering inferno in the heart of the capital on Friday. Led by a home ministry joint secretary, the probe body will look into the cause of the fire and report in seven work days, home secretary Abdus Sobhan Sikder told reporters from the spot in the afternoon. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina had earlier asked army, security agencies and all emergency rescue services to tackle the blazing fire and save the victims, her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters
